==FA Cup==
{{main|2014–15 FA Cup}}
United entered the FA Cup at the Third Round stage with the other Premier League clubs, as well as those from the [[2014–15 Football League Championship|Championship]]. The draw was made on 8 December 2014, which saw United drawn away at [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]] from [[Football League One|League One]].<ref>{{cite web |title=FA Cup Fixtures |url=http://www.thefa.com/thefacup/fixtures |website=TheFA.com |publisher=The Football Association |date=9 December 2014 |accessdate=9 December 2014 }}</ref> The match was played on 4 January 2015, with United winning 2–0 through second-half goals from [[Ander Herrera]] and [[Ángel Di María]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Yeovil 0–2 Man Utd |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30614400 |work=BBC Sport (British Broadcasting Corporation) |date=4 January 2015 |accessdate=4 January 2015 }}</ref> United went on to face [[Football League Two|League Two]] side [[Cambridge United F.C.|Cambridge United]] in the fourth round on 23 January 2015,<ref>{{cite news |first=Adam |last=Bostock |title=FA Cup: Reds to visit Cambridge United |url=http://www.manutd.com/en/News-And-Features/Football-News/2015/Jan/fa-cup-fourth-round-draw-for-manchester-united.aspx |website=ManUtd.com |publisher=Manchester United |date=5 January 2015 |accessdate=6 January 2015 }}</ref> but the match resulted in a goalless draw.<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Cambridge 0–0 Man Utd |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/30843611 |work=BBC Sport |date=23 January 2015 |accessdate=24 January 2015 }}</ref> The replay took place on 3 February at Old Trafford, with Manchester United winning 3–0, after goals from [[Juan Mata]], [[Marcos Rojo]] and [[James Wilson (footballer, born 1995)|James Wilson]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Tim |last=Rich |title=Tom Elliott has a shot at glory before visitors' FA Cup dream dies |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/fa-league-cups/manchester-united-vs-cambridge-united-match-report-tom-elliott-has-a-shot-at-glory-before-visitors-fa-cup-dream-dies-10022012.html |work=[[The Independent]] |date=3 February 2015 |accessdate=3 February 2015}}</ref> In the fifth round, United were drawn [[Deepdale|away]] to [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]], which they won 3–1. United had to come from behind after [[Scott Laird]] opened the scoring for Preston in the 47th minute. Ander Herrera levelled the game 18 minutes later, and [[Marouane Fellaini]] put United ahead in the 72nd minute. Near the end, [[Wayne Rooney]] scored a penalty to seal a place in the sixth round,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/31423124 |title=Preston 1–3 Man Utd |work=BBC Sport |date=16 February 2015 |accessdate=17 February 2015}}</ref> in which United were drawn in a home match to holders [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], which was played on 9 March 2015. United lost the match 2–1, resulting in the ''Red Devils''' exit from the FA Cup.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/31689011 |title=Manchester United 1–2 Arsenal |work=BBC Sport |date=9 March 2015 |accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>

