==League Cup==
{{main|2014–15 Football League Cup}}
United entered the League Cup at the Second Round stage for the first time since 1995–96, the last season before teams that had qualified for European competitions were allowed to enter the competition in the Third Round instead of the Second Round. The draw took place on 13 August 2014, with United being drawn away to [[Football League One|League One]] side [[Milton Keynes Dons F.C.|Milton Keynes Dons]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Capital One Cup Round 2 draw |url=http://www.capitalonecup.co.uk/news/article/20140813round2drawrp-1827422.aspx |work=capitalonecup.co.uk |publisher=The Football League |date=13 August 2014 |accessdate=17 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140817052805/http://www.capitalonecup.co.uk/news/article/20140813round2drawrp-1827422.aspx |archive-date=2014-08-17 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> It was the first ever meeting between the clubs, since the [[relocation of Wimbledon F.C. to Milton Keynes|formation of MK Dons]] in 2004. Manchester United were thrashed by their League One counterparts. [[Will Grigg]] scored twice to capitalise on defensive mistakes by the United back three, while substitute [[Benik Afobe]] added two further goals. It was United's earliest League Cup exit and first to a third-tier team since a 4–3 aggregate defeat to [[York City F.C.|York City]] of the [[Football League Second Division|Second Division]] back in 1995.

